{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T10:53:46.310Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Sequence Processing — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Sequence Processing Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Sequence processing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in Recurrent Neural Networks (RNNs) is the capability to handle data where the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "order matters"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and elements are inherently related to previous or future elements. Unlike feedforward neural networks that process each input independently, RNNs use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "loops to pass information from one step to the next"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", allowing them to process sequences of arbitrary length while retaining context."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "A "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "sequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is defined as an ordered list of objects, events, or data items."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Sequence Processing Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Sequence processing is fundamental to generative AI because most generative tasks involve creating ordered outputs:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Application"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Sequence Matters"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Text generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Words must follow grammatical/syntactical order"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language modeling"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Next word depends on all previous words"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Machine translation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input sentence → output sentence (different lengths)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Music generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Notes must follow temporal/harmonic relationships"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Image captioning"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Single image → sequence of descriptive words"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "RNNs are specifically structured for processing sequential data and are predominantly employed in Natural Language Processing (NLP)."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Sequence Processing Works (Core Mechanics)"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The key mechanism:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "RNNs use "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "parameter sharing"}, {"type": "text", "text": " — the repeated application of the same set of parameters across all time steps. This makes RNNs efficient for sequences, as the same logic is reused regardless of sequence length."}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "At each time step:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The network takes "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "two inputs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n1. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Current data point"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "x_t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (e.g., word in sentence, temperature reading)\n2. "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Hidden state from previous step"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "h_{t-1}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (memory summarizing past inputs)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "These are combined using weights and activation functions:"}]}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "h_t = f(W_{xh} \\cdot x_t + W_{hh} \\cdot h_{t-1} + b)"}}, {"type": "blockMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y_t = g(W_{hy} \\cdot h_t + c)"}}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where:\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "h_t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = new hidden state (updated memory)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "y_t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = output at time step "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "t"}}, {"type": "text", "text": "\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "W"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = weight matrices (shared across time)\n- "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "f, g"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " = activation functions"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The hidden state acts as memory:"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The hidden state captures information from previous steps and "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "influences how the network interprets subsequent inputs"}, {"type": "text", "text": ". For example, when analyzing a sentence, an RNN processes one word at a time, updating its hidden state to reflect the meaning up to that point."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Types of Sequence Processing Tasks"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Processing of a sequence may involve one or several operations:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Task Type"}]}]}